description: Recently sold: $641,800. Custom-built on a private, wooded lot overlooking Bailey School Forest Park, this distinctive home offers considerable living spaces, convenient main level living, and an outdoor space worth raving about.  The spacious floor plan starts in a two-story foyer with an open staircase, and to the right a grand living room with oversized windows, lending beautiful, wooded views, and a three-sided fireplace shared with the formal dining room.  Next door is the spacious kitchen with additional seating at a center island and informal dining area, lots of counter and cabinet space, and access to a vaulted three-season porch with a gas stove, perfect for entertaining, and surrounded by windows for more incredible views.  From here, a large deck wraps around the house to a rustic great room that boasts a vaulted wood ceiling and a floor-to-ceiling, stone surround, wood-burning fireplace.  Also conveniently located on the main level is the expansive master suite, offering a private upper level loft with a built-in workstation, wet bar, huge walk-in closet, and an en suite with in-floor heat, a tiled walk-in shower, and whirlpool tub beside a double-sided fireplace, where you can unwind the day.  On the upper level, you'll be pleased to find a huge loft with tons of built-ins for great storage space, three additional bedrooms with built-in workstations, a ¾ bath and full en suite bath.  The lower level then offers a walkout family room with another wood-burning fireplace, full wet bar with in-floor heat, an exercise room, fifth bedroom with a ¾ Jack & Jill walk-thru bath, and lastly, a relaxing sauna.  Outside, you can enjoy cookouts and bonfires on the patio or simply sit back and enjoy wildlife sightings from the upper and lower wrap-around decks.  This magnificent, one-owner property has been lovingly cared for since the day it was built and is ready for its new owners to make it their own.
